    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Ecclesiastes",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "To every thing there is a season\u2014Whatever God does, it will be forever\u2014God will judge the righteous and the wicked.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "To every thing there is a season, and a time to every purpose under the heaven:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 15:23.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Time.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A time to be born, and a time to die; a time to plant, and a time to pluck up that which is planted;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 17:26; Alma 40:10; D&C 138:53 (53\u201356).",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 20:1 (1\u20136); D&C 42:48.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A time to kill, and a time to heal; a time to break down, and a time to build up;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A time to weep, and a time to laugh; a time to mourn, and a time to dance;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laughter.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mourning.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A time to cast away stones, and a time to gather stones together; a time to embrace, and a time to refrain from embracing;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A time to get, and a time to lose; a time to keep, and a time to cast away;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0seek.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A time to rend, and a time to sew; a time to keep silence, and a time to speak;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 44:13.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Silence.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A time to love, and a time to hate; a time of war, and a time of peace.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "What profit hath he that worketh in that wherein he laboureth?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 29:15 (14\u201316).",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I have seen the travail, which God hath given to the sons of men to be exercised in it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0business, work, occupation, task.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 122:7 (5\u20137).",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He hath made every thing beautiful in his time: also he hath set the world in their heart, so that no man can find out the work that God maketh from the beginning to the end.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Beauty.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0He hath set the eternal in their heart without which man cannot find out the work that God hath done.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 8:17.",
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 127
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I know that there is no good in them, but for a man to rejoice, and to do good in his life.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 34:14.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And also that every man should eat and drink, and enjoy the good of all his labour, it is the gift of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Gifts of.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I know that, whatsoever God doeth, it shall be for ever: nothing can be put to it, nor any thing taken from it: and God doeth it, that men should fear before him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Celestial.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 10:18 (18\u201319).",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 5:7; Heb. 12:28; Mosiah 4:1.",
                        "start": 146,
                        "end": 150
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 129
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "That which hath been is now; and that which is to be hath already been; and God requireth that which is past.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 1:9.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And moreover I saw under the sun the place of judgment, that wickedness was there; and the place of righteousness, that iniquity was there.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "4\u00a0Ne. 1:44.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 119
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 132
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I said in mine heart, God shall judge the righteous and the wicked: for there is a time there for every purpose and for every work.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge; Judgment, the Last.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I said in mine heart concerning the estate of the sons of men, that God might manifest them, and that they might see that they themselves are beasts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0affairs.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 73:22.",
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 148
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For that which befalleth the sons of men befalleth beasts; even one thing befalleth them: as the one dieth, so dieth the other; yea, they have all one breath; so that a man hath no preeminence above a beast: for all is vanity.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 2:16.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 216,
                        "end": 218
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "All go unto one place; all are of the dust, and all turn to dust again.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 3:19.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who knoweth the spirit of man that goeth upward, and the spirit of the beast that goeth downward to the earth?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore I perceive that there is nothing better, than that a man should rejoice in his own works; for that is his portion: for who shall bring him to see what shall be after him?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 2:10.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 849
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}